---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Compare">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Compare</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-ink">
      Honest comparisons — PortixOne is early (MVP, Windows local printing only), so these are about
      helping you pick the right tool today, not claiming to already do more than we do.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-4">
      <a href="/compare/qz-tray" class="block rounded-lg border border-line p-5 hover:border-white/20">
        <p class="font-medium">PortixOne vs QZ Tray</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/compare/jsprintmanager" class="block rounded-lg border border-line p-5 hover:border-white/20">
        <p class="font-medium">PortixOne vs JSPrintManager</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-muted">
      Full landscape of bridges and browser printing APIs:
      <a href="https://github.com/portixhq/awesome-web-printing" class="hover:text-ink">awesome-web-printing</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
